.TH "hcd_buffer_create" 9 "hcd_buffer_create" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hcd_buffer_create \- initialize buffer pools
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hcd_buffer_create
.BI "(struct usb_hcd *hcd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hcd" 12
the bus whose buffer pools are to be initialized
.SH "CONTEXT"
task context, might sleep
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Call this as part of initializing a host controller that uses the dma
memory allocators.  It initializes some pools of dma-coherent memory that
will be shared by all drivers using that controller.

Call \fBhcd_buffer_destroy\fP to clean up after using those pools.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful. A negative errno value otherwise.
